# View models (iOS 2026 template)

## Dependency injection

- Mark the initializer with **`@Resolvable`** so Knit can generate factory wiring.
- Register each view model type in the app assembly’s **`registerViewModels(container:)`** (in `Service/App/*Assembly.swift`), alongside other registrations.

## Observation

- Declare view models with **`@Observable`** (import `Observation` if needed). SwiftUI views should take the model with **`@Bindable`** when bindings are required.

## Navigation

- Perform navigation through the **ASKCoordinator** stack (e.g. coordinator / path APIs exposed via injection), not ad hoc `NavigationLink` targets or one-off routers. Keep coordinator usage consistent with existing `CoordinatorPath` / renderer patterns in `Scene/Coordinator/`.
- Create a new CoordinatorPath entry for each View/ViewModel pair and always use this when displaying the view.
- Do not use `NavigationStack` directly in Views, always use `CoordinatorView` with a path

## State exposed to views

- **Do not** expose data to SwiftUI through methods the view calls only to read state (e.g. `func title() -> String`). Anything the view displays or binds must live on **`var`** properties (including computed vars when derived state is still property-based).
- Methods are fine for **actions** (user intents, navigation, async work), not as the primary way to **read** model state.

```swift
// ❌ BAD — view must call functions to read UI state
func displayName() -> String { user.name }

// ✅ GOOD — view reads properties
var userName: String
```
